
Use http://asciimath.org/ to show the equations


Math:
-----

Solving the equation of the 2D projection of the magnetic pendulum:

ddot(vec(r)) = vec(F_g) + vec(F_m) + vec(F_r)

vec(F_g) = grad(vec(g)*vec(r))
vec(F_m) = - grad(sum(V_i(vec(r))))
vec(F_r) = - gamma * dot(vec(r))

V_i = alpha_i / abs(vec(r) - vec(r_i))^b

-> ddot(vec(r)) = grad(vec(g)*vec(r)) - grad(sum(V_i(vec(r)))) - gamma * dot(vec(r))

vec(F_g): "RÃ¼cktriebskraft" (Force pulling back the pendulum to the middle)
vec(F_m): "Magnetkraft" (Resulting magnetical force considering all magnets)
vec(F_r): "Reibungskraft" (Force of the friction affecting the motion)

vec(r)(t): Position of the pendulum at time t
vec(g): Middle point of the pendulum (0, 0)
vec(r_i): Position of a magnet

alpha_i: Strength of the magnet
b: Magnet attenuation with distance
gamma: Strength of the friction


Sources:
--------

